all points that we want to make, both posi-
tive and negative.”

Other members said that the meeting
was productive.

“We each needed to learn things from
the other, and I think it was very helpful in
that regard, but that’s all I’H say,” said David
Gauthier, another committee member.

Provost James Maher would not com-
