courses as possible in other depart-
ments. These classes have expanded
my horizon, helped me revise, and
given me new philosophies on my
approach to just about
everything. It is liber-
ating and a great men-
tal health break for
someone who hasn’t
seen the outside of
Benedum in a great
while. Concepts taught
in philosophy can even
give one a new look on
his career in engineer-
ing. Ethics are espe-
cially of interest to engineers because
once out in the work force and the
corporate world, scientists and engi-
neers make moral decisions every
day. It is the nature of society.

On the same note, I think there

.are a few things that humanities

majors should know about technolo-
gy. Computer literacy is a big one.
Word processors and spreadsheets are
wonderful time-saving tools. The
time taken to learn these things is
paid back tenfold by the timed saved
by using them. Furthermore, the

